=== LFS 12.4 STRIPPING BUG - IMPORTANT NOTE FOR 12.4 USERS ===
Date: $(date)

PROBLEM:
The stripping script in LFS 12.4 (§8.83) strips libbfd-2.45.so and
libsframe.so in-place using --strip-unneeded. Since strip itself depends
on libbfd at runtime, stripping libbfd while it is loaded corrupts it to
zero bytes. This cascades - strip then fails on every subsequent file,
and ld-linux-x86-64.so.2 (the ELF loader) was also zeroed, rendering
the system unbootable.

ROOT CAUSE:
LFS 12.4 strip script processes online_usrlib files in-place.
LFS 13.0 fixes this by copying to /tmp first, stripping there,
then reinstalling with the install command - same safe approach
used for save_usrlib.

RECOVERY STEPS TAKEN:
1. Rebuilt libbfd-2.45.so using host gcc on /mnt/lfs from outside chroot
2. Restored ld-linux-x86-64.so.2 from backup image lfs-ch8-complete.img
3. Re-ran stripping using corrected 13.0-style script (copy-to-tmp method)

FIX FOR 12.4 USERS:
Replace the online_usrlib loop in §8.83 with:
    for LIB in $online_usrlib; do
        cp /usr/lib/$LIB /tmp/$LIB
        strip --strip-debug /tmp/$LIB
        install -vm755 /tmp/$LIB /usr/lib
        rm /tmp/$LIB
    done
Use --strip-debug instead of --strip-unneeded throughout.

LESSON: Always make a backup image before running the strip step.
=== END NOTE ===
